<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Witty" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Witty,</orth> 1) wise, discreet: <cit><quote>it is the --est partition that ever I heard discourse,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 168</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>better a w. fool than a foolish wit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 39</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>she'll come straight, you must be w. now,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 32</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) cunning, artful: <cit><quote>a marvellous w. fellow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 2, 27</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the deep-revolving w. Buckingham,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 2, 42</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) possessed of wit, full of pleasant conceits: <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.266" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 266</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 4, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 2, 43</bibl>. H8 Epil. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 2, 43</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 132</bibl>.

